OSD_definition: This term is from the 1991 Sega Genesis release of an arcade game called "Zero Wing."  The introduction in the game has a very poor translation of Japanese to English.  It shows the bridge of a space ship in chaos as the enemy appears and says, "How are you gentlemen!!  All your base are belong to us."In 2001, this poor translation spread virally through the Internet, resulting in many images of doctored photographs, each showing a street sign, store front, package label, etc. manipulated to read "All your base are belong to us."The original has been generalized to "All your \'X\' are belong to us", to imply that the thing \'X\' will be annihilated. LLM_definition: Gaining a win or advantage by sheer chance or fortuity, especially when not initially favored.
OSD_definition: to achieve something by accident.  To win against extreme odds usually when more fancied competitors have eliminated themselves from a contest because of unforeseen circumstances.  Also, to plan to run last in an event as a tactical move to capitalize on any mishaps that may occur.  Origin: Steven Bradbury, a short course speed ice skater representing Australia at the 2002  winter Olympics won Gold after all 6 of the more fancied competitors in front of him fell on the final corner.  Bradbury in last place, skated 10 metres past the fallen skaters to win gold.  Bradbury believed that he would not be able to win so remained in last place and waited for a mishap to occur, which it did, allowing him to win Australia's first ever winter Olympic gold medal.  Australian slang.

OSD_definition: The Great Northern Railway (now a part of the BNSF Railroad) constructed a tunnel in the Cascades mountains in Washington in the early 1900s.  The railroad set up construction camps at various locations along the line.  Each camp had an adminstrative building with the Great Northern flag displayed out front.  The logo for the GN railroad was the mountain goat, which was used in advertising, painted on freight and passenger cars, etc.  In time, there developed competition between the camps for the best performance - most miles of track laid, bridges built, etc.  From time to time, one camp would raid another and take their flag, which of course upset the camp that lost its flag with the goat logo.  Thus the phrase "get my goat."

LLM_definition: A whimsical term to express bewilderment or a lack of understanding.
usage_context: She was talking about quantum physics and I was just sitting there, quizzlepuff! | He started explaining the rules to the game, and I was like, quizzlepuff all the way through.

LLM_definition: A confirmation of understanding, often accompanied by a physical nod; used to signify agreement or acknowledgment of heard information.
OSD_definition: acronym for "heard that".  A statement of agreement.
usage_context: Person A: I think we should order pizza tonight. | Person B: Noted 'N Nodded, pizza it is!

LLM_definition: A playful and affectionate term for a husband.
usage_context: Emma referred to her husband as her hubster when telling stories about their travels. | On their anniversary, Jack wrote a sweet message to his hubster, Mike, on social media.

LLM_definition: Exclamation used to convey attraction, suggesting that someone is of high value and quality.
usage_context: Wow, did you see Jamie today? Total fine-dine vibes! | Just bumped into Sam; they're looking pretty fine-dine this evening!

LLM_definition: A vivid or colorful act of vomiting, typically due to mixed or excessive alcohol consumption.
OSD_definition: Same as; hurl, blow chips, chunks, cheese, barf, spew, blow chowder, ralph.
usage_context: After that wild party, he performed a technicolor yawn all over the sidewalk. | I knew she had one too many cocktails when she started to technicolor yawn by the curb.

LLM_definition: An expert snowboarder, especially talented in performing complex spin tricks.
OSD_definition: A snowboarder who does spin tricks well, also used to describe any snowboarder of any talent may also be 'huckster'.
usage_context: Zoe's reputation as a trickologist really shows when she’s shredding the slopes. | You can always spot a trickologist by how smoothly they handle spins.

LLM_definition: n. 1. a person or group that is of preference. 2. The person who can get the job done. 3. Someone liked. 'the go-to man.'
OSD_definition: n. 1.a person or group that is of preference. 2. The person or people who can get the job done. 3. Someone liked. "the go-to man."
usage_context: In the kitchen, Marco is the star player, whipping up gourmet dishes effortlessly. | When it comes to brainstorming, Nina is the star player on our team.

LLM_definition: To exhale forcefully when filled with anger, resembling a dragon's fiery breath.

usage_context: As the injustice of the situation sank in, he released a dragon's exhale. | The toddler's constant screaming made her let out a dragon's exhale in exasperation.

LLM_definition: A playful nod to a celebrity chef's prowess, used to reference a penis.
OSD_definition: a penis.  Also derides the celebrity chef, Hugh Fearnley-Whittingstall.

LLM_definition: An informal term used to depict something as massive or extraordinarily large.

LLM_definition: Looking or being extremely ugly.

LLM_definition: The act of vomiting into a toilet while kneeling, usually after heavy drinking.
OSD_definition: to be on one\'s knees vomiting into a toilet.  The person is usually drunk so they are holding on to the sides of the toilet, hence "hugging the toilet".

LLM_definition: Used to acknowledge that the speaker has received and understood the information.
OSD_definition: when used as a statement, "I see."

LLM_definition: To reek of marijuana.

LLM_definition: An energetic process where an audience loudly repeats what a speaker says, allowing the message to carry further.
OSD_definition: the loud repetition of a speaker's words by members of a crowd, such that the speaker's words are audible over a longer distance.
usage_context: To ensure clarity, the march leaders initiated a shout loop for every important announcement. | With the aid of a shout loop, the assembly's chants became a unified, resonating call for change.

LLM_definition: A colloquial expression for human feces, playing on the idea of dropping waste.

LLM_definition: A humorous, imaginary cupcake symbolizing a mistake one must admit.
OSD_definition: a metaphorical type of pie that a person "eats" when they are proven wrong in a spectacular way, are are aware that they have been proven wrong, and accept that they were wrong.
usage_context: After insisting that she knew the correct route, Lydia was left with a crow cupcake when they got hopelessly lost. | Bob swallowed a crow cupcake during the meeting when his figures were proven inaccurate.

LLM_definition: A courteous way of asking for clarification or repetition of what was just spoken.
usage_context: Excuse me? I must have misheard you over the noise.

LLM_definition: A polite request for someone to repeat what they have just said.
usage_context: Pardon me? I didn't catch the last part of your sentence.

LLM_definition: Informal slang indicating a session of oral sex, often used to lighten the topic.
usage_context: She gave him a whistle blow that left him grinning from ear to ear. | Rumor has it he scored a whistle blow at the party.

LLM_definition: An individual in the process of growing their awareness and understanding of humanity's role on Earth.
OSD_definition: A human who is learning to live as one with humanity and earth.Pronunciation: hyoo`mon Roots: hum (earth, man), mon (one)
usage_context: Mark is a real humansprout; he just joined that community garden to learn more about urban farming. | Ever since Jane moved to the countryside, she's been a humansprout, soaking up knowledge about living naturally.

LLM_definition: Extremely large; even more so than gigantic or enormous.
usage_context: The statue in the park is absolutely ginormo, towering over the trees. | Did you see that ginormo bear on the nature documentary? It was huge!

LLM_definition: Someone who moves or acts sluggishly, exhibiting minimal effort.
OSD_definition: a lazy or worthless person.This definition is questionable and is pending deletion.  It will be saved from deletion if legitimate citations are found.
usage_context: Every time we ask Jess to hang out, she's a total slack slug and never joins. | Come on, slack slug, it's time to get moving and enjoy the sunshine!

LLM_definition: Exceptionally great in size or intensity.
OSD_definition: immense.  First appeared in print in 1976.
usage_context: The mega-mondo burger at the restaurant comes with eight patties! It's a beast to tackle. | Her wedding was a mega-mondo affair, with hundreds of guests and an endless feast.

LLM_definition: A sweet term used for someone precious and delightful.
OSD_definition: a term of endearment for a loved one.
usage_context: Hey sugarplum, are you free for dinner tonight? | My sugarplum has the sweetest smile I've ever seen.

LLM_definition: Slang for one hundred, referencing the $100 bill often called a 'Benjamin' due to the portrait of Benjamin Franklin.
usage_context: I'll lend you a benjamin if you promise to pay me back. | Wow, this concert ticket is costing me a whole benjamin!

LLM_definition: A quick acknowledgment of total agreement.
usage_context: Person A: Should we order pizza for dinner? | Person B: S'right.

LLM_definition: An expression used to describe being much later than anticipated, as if the time has ghosted the schedule.
OSD_definition: very late.  Typically later than one expected it to be.

LLM_definition: A large collection or sum of hundred-dollar bills.
usage_context: She's saving up, got a whole stack-a-hunnids tucked away. | When he wins at poker, he always ends up with a stack-a-hunnids.

LLM_definition: Implying one possesses a long and large penis, comparable to a giraffe's leg.
OSD_definition: having a large penis.  Also "well hung", "hung like [a specific animal]" (e.g. "hung like a horse").
usage_context: Jake's confident strut earned him the nickname 'giraffe leg' among his friends. | No wonder she's always smiling, her boyfriend's got a 'giraffe leg'.

LLM_definition: An overwhelming surge of hunger
usage_context: Out of nowhere, I was hit by an appetite tsunami, and I devoured my entire lunch. | The aroma from the bakery started an appetite tsunami inside me.

LLM_definition: A playful reference to Benjamin Franklin, whose face appears on the $100 bill.
OSD_definition: One hundred dollars, or a one hundred dollar bill.  Also hungie.

LLM_definition: The appearance of abdominal muscles due to extreme thinness rather than fitness.
OSD_definition: a six pack that's a result of emaciation rather than exercise.

LLM_definition: A state of seeking refuge or isolation in anticipation of an unfavorable situation, as if retreating into a personal bunker.
OSD_definition: To dig in or crouch for the purpose of waiting out or avoiding an undesirable event or situation.

LLM_definition: An affectionate version of 'honey', used informally among friends and loved ones.
usage_context: Can't wait to see you later, huni! | What's up, huni?

LLM_definition: A person who consistently dismisses and overrides others' viewpoints, often in a debate or discussion.

LLM_definition: Referring to an object or being so massive it breaks the usual scale; typically refers to something bulky or grand in size.

LLM_definition: A dismissive mimicry of speech indicating perceived ignorance.

LLM_definition: Completely inebriated to the point of losing focus or coherence.

LLM_definition: An individual who thinks they have smooth charisma but falls short.

OSD_definition: same as bling bling or word.

LLM_definition: To have or keep something in one's possession.
usage_context: He's always got a stash of snacks hidden in his drawer. | If you've got the stash, bring it to the party.

LLM_definition: Refers to the routine and sometimes tedious work done at a desk to complete homework tasks.

LLM_definition: Artificially cultivated marijuana, often involving nutrient-rich water systems.

LLM_definition: A boyfriend found and interacted with mainly through web platforms, remaining virtual.

LLM_definition: Acronym for 'I don't know?' conveying uncertainty and slight annoyance.

usage_context:
Jenna: Do you remember where I left my keys? 
Tom: IDK?, I've been looking everywhere! | I've been trying to figure out what the boss meant all day. IDK? at this point.

LLM_definition: A grueling or unappealing duty that each person must take turns performing, especially one that's physically exhausting.

In the military, it is sometimes referred to doing KP, but in times of combat, might have been used to mean taking on a very dangerous chore such as walking point on recon.There is a vulgar joke associated with the phrase about soldiers putting their penises through a hole in a barrel to receive oral sex. I\'m not sure if the vulgar joke is the source of the phrase. LLM_definition: A time when only night owls are still active, spanning from midnight until the first light of dawn.
OSD_definition: a very late - or very early - time of the day.  Some unspecified time between midnight and dawn.
usage_context: She prefers working during the owl's stretch, when distractions are at their minimum. | During the owl's stretch, only the sound of crickets and distant traffic can be heard.

LLM_definition: A witty but unkind retort or teasing comment.
usage_context: After the meeting, he had a quibber ready for each of their ideas. | Watch out for his quibbers; they're sharp and on point.

LLM_definition: An Israeli who lives in a dream world, believing that negotiations with hostile groups will result in lasting peace.
OSD_definition: An Israeli who believes that it is possible to make lasting and secure peace with a terrorist or Arab group whose stated goal is to kill him and destroy his country.
usage_context: Yoel's dreamicratic outlook is admirable, but perhaps a little unrealistic given the current tensions. | Calling for more talks, she's often labeled a dreamicratic, as many see her stance as wishful thinking.

LLM_definition: A gadget or any unknown object with a vague description.
usage_context: This gizmo is supposed to help you open jars more easily. | He always carries around some gizmo or other in his bag.

LLM_definition: To intentionally choose not to speak or communicate.
OSD_definition: to be quiet.  Also zip it.
usage_context: After receiving the hint, she went into mute mode until the meeting was over. | He prefers to hit mute mode during disagreements rather than argue.

LLM_definition: Someone with a visible head scar, generally from a previous encounter or surgery.
OSD_definition: a person with a pronounced scar visible on their head.  Said scar is generally incurred from some sort of surgery, often from an altercation in a bar room, generally acquired by contact with a broken beer bottle.
usage_context: Tom wears his 'Scar Cap' like a badge of honor from his daring adventures. | They call her 'Scar Cap' ever since she returned from that fateful vacation with a new look.

LLM_definition: A playful way to refer to a pimple, likening it to a mischievous creature on the skin.
usage_context: I need to get rid of this skin gremlin before the party tonight! | Every time I'm stressed, a new skin gremlin shows up on my chin.

LLM_definition: An unexpected or surprising occurrence, often said with a hint of disbelief.
OSD_definition: an exclamation of surprise or shock.  Popularized by the Scooby Doo cartoon.
usage_context: Blorple! Where did that raccoon come from? | She dropped her ice cream on the floor and shouted, 'Blorple!'

LLM_definition: An exclamation used to convey extreme astonishment, blending traditional surprise with an explosive twist.
OSD_definition: "Oh my fucking God."  Expresses a greater level of amazement or elation than the standard OMFG.
usage_context: Holy guacamole rocket, I can't believe you got front-row tickets! | That performance was incredible. Holy guacamole rocket!

LLM_definition: An amusing and heightened expression of amazement, derived from the slang of disbelief and humor.
OSD_definition: "Oh my God."  Expresses a greater level of amazement or elation than the standard OMG.  Like all words, can be used either sincerely or not sincerely.
usage_context: Sweet Jeebus, you actually aced that test? | When I saw the cake, all I could say was 'Sweet Jeebus!'

LLM_definition: In a state of absentmindedness, where one's focus and presence are completely lacking.
OSD_definition: very intoxicated; spacey.  Also zoned out.  A "zone trooper" is someone apt to be in this state.
usage_context: He's been so spaced out since the meeting started, he hasn't heard a word anyone said. | I was spaced out after the long flight, barely noticing my surroundings.

LLM_definition: To mentally drift away from the present situation or task.
OSD_definition: zone out - to lose control of one's focus.
usage_context: She went on a space cruise during the meeting and couldn't answer the question. | I need a break; I've been on a space cruise for the last half hour.

LLM_definition: In a state of extreme intoxication, often from consuming alcohol or drugs.
OSD_definition: extremely intoxicated.  Usually refers to alcohol intoxication but can also apply to marijuana or other drugs.
usage_context: He got blitzed at the party last night and doesn’t remember a thing. | Every time there's a celebration, they end up blitzed before the night's over.

LLM_definition: An unforeseen smooch that catches someone off guard.
OSD_definition: an unexpected and usually undesirable kiss.
usage_context: In the middle of the conversation, he pulled a smooch ambush on her. | The festival was fun until some stranger tried a smooch ambush; it was awkward.

LLM_definition: Bottom-half of a fursuit costume, primarily covering legs and paws.
OSD_definition: a furry costume; "fursuit".  From the "furry" subculture.
usage_context: The design of those paw-pants is so realistic; they even have articulated claws! | She ordered custom paw-pants to match her top half, and they look amazing together.

LLM_definition: Heavily affected by the consumption of pills, often impairing cognitive functions.
usage_context: Mark was cap rocked from the medication, he could hardly keep track of time. | Be careful, those capsules can leave you completely cap rocked for hours.

LLM_definition: A suffix used to give an air of mechanical or high-tech intensity.
OSD_definition: suffix used with a word to intensify it.  Frequently used in collaboration with (and originated from) "leet speak" (1337).  Also -zorness, -zors.
usage_context: The new laptop she got is pure speed-tron! | This concert is going to be party-tron with all the light shows planned.

LLM_definition: An informal way to describe sandals that make a clacking noise due to the straps that rest between the toes.
usage_context: She slipped into her toe clackers for a quick stroll down the boardwalk. | You can't sneak around with those toe clackers; they announce your arrival!

LLM_definition: To take a short, light sleep or nap.
OSD_definition: sleep.  Used in expressions such as catch some z's, get some z's.
usage_context: She felt refreshed after grabbing a snooze on the couch. | I've got some free time; I might just grab a snooze before dinner.

LLM_definition: A thrilling rope swing setup next to a swimming spot for an adrenaline rush.
OSD_definition: a rope swing next to a body of water (such as a river or swimming pool.)
usage_context: Dare to take the rope rip over the river and experience an epic plunge? | She shouted with glee as she soared on the rope rip, splashing down into the pool.

LLM_definition: A passionate enthusiast who has an in-depth knowledge of hops and their impact on beer flavors.
OSD_definition: The study of beer and beer-making, including the role particular ingredients play in the brewing process.  A zythologist is a student and connoisseur of beer who possess knowledge of ingredients, pouring techniques and beer pairings.  From Greek zythos (beer) + logos (study).
usage_context: Sandra's been a hop-head since she attended her first beer-tasting event; she can differentiate varieties just by their aroma. | Only a hop-head like Tim would plan his vacation around visiting hop farms and breweries.
